<p>Creating wireframes to outline user flow was prepared in Sketch without the inclusion of visual aesthetics; some would also call this the "gray box technique." Each series of questions were examined carefully to assist in indentifying the best way for displaying information, and providing efficiency in regards to feedback and iterations. The ability to <a href="https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2017/04/symbols-sketch">create symbols in Sketch</a> was certainly an ally throughout the process.</p>

